The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Oct. 3: Sun Pharmaceutical has said the last date for its open offer to purchase all outstanding shares of Taro Pharmaceutical had been extended to November 7, in compliance with the Israel supreme court order. The open offer is now scheduled to expire on November 7, the company said in a statement.                            
	 Mumbai, Oct. 3: Emami has revised the open offer price for purchasing a 20 per cent stake in Zandu to Rs 16,500 per share.The announcement came within a fortnight after Emami doubled the offer price to Rs 15,000 per share from the initial Rs 7,315 apiece.                            
	 New Delhi, Oct. 3: Jubilant Organosys and Eli Lilly will form a joint venture (JV) to provide drug development services for the medicines developed by both the companies, besides those of third parties. Both companies will invest $4 million each in the next three years in the proposed JV.                            
	 New Delhi, Oct. 3: The government has asked sugar mills to sell the sweetener from the second buffer stocks, according to a quarter-wise schedule, instead of selling at any time in the 2008-09.                            
	 New Delhi, Oct. 3: Banks will get an interest of over Rs 3,500 crore on their outgo for the farm debt waiver scheme from the second installment of such reimbursements due in 2009.                                                                                                                         
